<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Twitter defense</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/27418577.257595/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTgvdHdpdHRlci1oYXMtYS1wb2lzb24tcGlsbC1ub3c_=
Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxOTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5=
ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDE5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB5f0f158d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> talked yesterday</a> about Twitter Inc.=
=E2=80=99s takeover defenses against Elon Musk=E2=80=99s vague proposal to =
buy it. Or, rather, we talked about the poison pill that Twitter=E2=80=99s =
board of directors put in place to stop Musk. That=E2=80=99s the main takeo=
ver defense, in that it prevents Musk from buying more shares without negot=
iating with the board. But Twitter is actually pretty well defended against=
 a hostile bid.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In modern U.S. hostile take=
overs, the main way that a hostile bidder can fight back against a poison p=
ill goes like this:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left:=
 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Launch a tende=
r offer to buy 100% of the company=E2=80=99s stock directly from shareholde=
rs. The tender offer should be real =E2=80=94=C2=A0with firm financing line=
d up =E2=80=94=C2=A0and fair to all shareholders. (It should be be for 100%=
 of the stock, it should let everyone get cash if they want, it should=C2=
=A0promise that if the bidder gets control of the company any second-step m=
erger will be on the same terms, etc.) But the tender offer will be conting=
ent on getting rid of the poison pill, which otherwise would make the bidde=
r=E2=80=99s shares go poof; you can=E2=80=99t close the tender offer while =
the pill is in place.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Launch a pro=
xy fight to replace the board of directors who are standing in the way of t=
he bid with some friendlier set of directors who will get rid of the pill a=
nd let the tender offer close.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The te=
nder offer asks shareholders to sell their shares to the bidder;=C2=A0the p=
roxy fight=C2=A0asks shareholders to=C2=A0<em>vote=C2=A0</em>their shares f=
irst to get rid of the board and let the tender offer close.</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Will Elon Musk do this? I dunno. There are two problems:<=
/p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px =
0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">To launch a tender offer, he will =
need to write a detailed securities filing committing him to buy the stock =
and detailing his plans and financing. If he has no financing and is just w=
inging this, or if he doesn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>want to buy=
 all the stock, that will be hard.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>Twitter is structurally well protected from a proxy fight. It has a classi=
fied board, meaning that only about one-third of directors are up for elect=
ion at each annual meeting, so he can=E2=80=99t replace the whole board and=
 get rid of the pill. Also this year=E2=80=99s annual meeting is on May 25,=
 he=E2=80=99s=C2=A0too late to run his own candidates, and Twitter=E2=80=99=
s charter doesn=E2=80=99t allow shareholders to call special meetings to el=
ect directors. So he won=E2=80=99t be able to get a majority of the board t=
hrough proxy fighting until about 2024.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">Still he could gesture in that direction, if he wanted to. Bloomberg New=
s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27418577.257595/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTgvdHdpdHR=
lci1nYWlucy1hcy1pdC1wbG90cy1kZWZlbnNlLXN0cmF0ZWd5LWFnYWluc3QtbXVzay10YWtlb3=
Zlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDE5MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY=
2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA0MTkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe719845d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> explains the situation</a>:</p><blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If Musk is serious about pushing ahead=
 with his takeover offer for Twitter, he should launch a tender offer to ac=
quire the shares in the company he doesn=E2=80=99t already own despite the =
poison pill, said Andrew Freedman, co-chair of the shareholder activism pra=
ctice at law firm Olshan Frome Wolosky.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=
=80=9CEven though Musk wouldn=E2=80=99t be able to close his tender offer, =
even with a majority of shares tendered, given the poison pill and other im=
pediments, it=E2=80=99s a =E2=80=98put your money where your mouth is=E2=80=
=99 type move and shows he really wants to buy this company,=E2=80=9D Freed=
man said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk could simultaneously launch =
a proxy contest where he would ask shareholders to withhold their votes for=
 the two directors who will stand for re-election at this year=E2=80=99s an=
nual meeting, which is slated for May 25, Freedman said. That would serve a=
s a referendum on his offer, and also allow him to solicit votes for an ame=
ndment to the company=E2=80=99s charter to declassify the board, meaning th=
at all directors would stand for election each year rather than just a few,=
 he added. Last year, a similar proposal almost achieved the 80% vote thres=
hold required to change the company=E2=80=99s bylaws, he noted.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If Musk doesn=E2=80=99t act in the next few months, he=
 won=E2=80=99t be able to do much at Twitter until next year=E2=80=99s annu=
al general meeting because the company doesn=E2=80=99t allow for shareholde=
rs to call a special meeting or act by written consent.=C2=A0</p></blockquo=
te><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Note that the =E2=80=9Cproxy contest=E2=80=
=9D here would mostly symbolic, not about replacing the board so that he co=
uld do his deal but just about signaling to the board that shareholders=C2=
=A0<em>want=C2=A0</em>to let him do his deal. It is not particularly clear =
to me that they do, but they might. And if the board got a strong signal th=
at this is what shareholders want =E2=80=94=C2=A0from symbolic and structur=
al votes at the annual meeting, or just from big shareholders calling the b=
oard to say =E2=80=9Cwe like Elon=E2=80=99s deal=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0it=
 would not be=C2=A0<em>obligated=C2=A0</em>to take Musk=E2=80=99s deal, but=
 it might feel some pressure to.=C2=A0A hostile takeover of Twitter is poss=
ible, but it would be a grinding drawn-out fight, and it=E2=80=99s possible=
 that Musk would prefer to tweet mean things about the board rather than do=
 the fighting.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27418577.257595/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcn=
RpY2xlcy9hcG9sbG8tZ2xvYmFsLWNvbnNpZGVycy1wYXJ0aWNpcGF0aW5nLWluLWJpZC1mb3Itd=
HdpdHRlci0xMTY1MDMxMzAxMz9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3M2/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd6=
65d834" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">Elsewhere</a>:=C2=A0</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">Apollo Global Management Inc. is considering participating in a bid f=
or Twitter Inc., according to people familiar with the matter, after Elon M=
usk=E2=80=99s $43 billion bid put the social-media company in play.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Apollo, one of the world=E2=80=99s largest buyout =
firms, has held discussions about backing a possible deal for Twitter and c=
ould provide Mr. Musk or another bidder like private-equity firm Thoma Brav=
o LP with equity or debt to support an offer, the people said.</p></blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is an estimate that Twitter could sup=
port <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27418577.2575=
95/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTIv=
d2lsbC1lbG9uLW11c2stYnV5LW1vcmUtdHdpdHRlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDE5MjJfTU9ORVlTVFV=
GRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA0MT=
kmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd5755c11" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
