-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> about $10 billion of debt</a>, which is a little slim for a=C2=A0$40 bil=
lion or $50 billion buyout but is something at least. I suppose there is so=
me chance that if you lend to a Musk Twitter buyout, the cash flows won=E2=
=80=99t support the debt (especially after Musk removes content moderation =
and advertisers leave), Musk will get bored, the debt will default and you=
=E2=80=99ll end up owning Twitter for $10 billion. I=E2=80=99m not sure if =
you=E2=80=99d want that.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-flex-ad" border=3D"0=
